OL,3,CPeacemaker told killer to stop
OL,4,Cfighting before fatal punch
OL,6,F"The last words he was overheard to
OL,7,Fsay were addressed to the man who
OL,8,Fkilled him, and only seconds before it
OL,9,Fhappened."
OL,11,FA guest at the pub that night heard
OL,12,Fhim say to Egan, referring to his
OL,13,Ffriend: "Stop fighting, he's drunk,
OL,14,Fplease, please, he doesn't mean it."
OL,16,FEgan and Barnfield deny murdering Mr
OL,17,FHallatt.
OL,19,FThe trial continues.
